            "created_at": "2016-08-30T16:08:50Z",
            "updated_at": "2016-09-19T15:08:34Z",
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Wow @untitaker - that was fast.\n@taion: Well, for one thing the flask cli is designed to be used for any arbitrary task that could be run in prod (starting with db mgt with `Flask-Alembic`...). It's supposed to be a saner replacement for the deprecated `manager` of `Flask-Script`, and limiting its usage to dev environments seems sad to me. For two, even if `pip install -e .` is 'reasonable', it's just not documented - hence my remark.\n\nUnless we just make `python -m flask` the recommended way to go?\n"
        },
